This paper proposes a new approach for learning knowledge graph embeddings using word embeddings, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves learning low-dimensional representations, which is a common task in machine learning and data mining, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and databases, indicating that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible sub-categories.
